  "prompt": "Where can I find a training data set (free or not) for patent/prior art search to train a deep learning engine to select relevant prior art/ patents?",
  "response": "Here are several resources for patent and prior art datasets:\n\nFree Datasets:\n1. USPTO Patent Dataset\n- Official US Patent and Trademark Office datasets\n- Public domain\n- Various formats available\n- https://www.uspto.gov/learning-and-resources/bulk-data-downloads\n\n2. Google Patents Public Datasets\n- Large collection of patent documents\n- Free access\n- https://datasetsearch.research.google.com/\n\n3. Kaggle Patent Datasets\n- Community-contributed patent collections\n- Some free datasets\n- https://www.kaggle.com/datasets?search=patent\n\nPaid/Commercial Datasets:\n1. Clarivate Innovation Intelligence\n- Comprehensive patent database\n- Structured data\n- https://clarivate.com/\n\n2. PatBase\n- Global patent database\n- Paid subscription\n- https://www.patbase.com/\n\n3. Espacenet (European Patent Office)\n- Large international patent collection\n- Some free, some paid tiers\n- https://worldwide.espacenet.com/\n\nSpecialized Research Resources:\n1. IEEE Xplore Digital Library\n2. Thomson Innovation\n3. Derwent World Patents Index\n\nRecommendation: Start with free datasets, validate your approach, then consider commercial sources.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these resources?",
